"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-football-emma-hayes-usa-olympics-2024-b1160744.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Football  Emma Hayestook charge of her first training session as boss of theUSAovernight as they step up their preparations for this summer's Olympics.  Hayes was confirmed as the new head coach of the USA back in November, but she agreed to finish the season with Chelsea and led them to afifth straight Women's Super League title.  The 47-year-old has now got to work with the USA and oversaw her first training session in Colorado.  Hayes was putting the players through their paces ahead of her first game in charge, which is against the Korea Republic on Saturday.  The USA will play them again three days later and the double header is viewed as vital preparation on the road to this summer's Olympics in Paris.  Hayes is looking to end the USA's 12-year wait to win gold in the women's football and her new squad cannot wait to work with her.  \\\"She's a legend and her resume speaks for itself,\\\" said USA forward Sophia Smith. \\\"Anyone in the soccer world knows Emma Hayes.  \\\"I am sure we will learn a lot in the next week. We already have learned a lot in the first few days.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"